This paper focuses on privacy-preserving distributed machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses differential privacy, which is a subfield of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of the alternating direction method of multipliers (ADMM) suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of optimization (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the tradeoff between privacy and accuracy, which is a topic that falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and the design of optimal privacy mechanisms, which is a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
